{
  "local_port": 54994,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I set .htacces file for solving canonical issues and image expiry issue in .aspx websites? As apache server don't support .htaccess file.",
  "response": "For .aspx websites running on IIS (Internet Information Services), you'll need to use web.config instead of .htaccess. Here's a comprehensive example that addresses canonical issues and image expiry:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<configuration>\n    <system.webServer>\n        <!-- Canonical URL Redirects -->\n        <rewrite>\n            <rules>\n                <!-- Redirect non-www to www -->\n                <rule name=\"Redirect to www\" stopProcessing=\"true\">\n                    <match url=\".*\" />\n                    <conditions>\n                        <add input=\"{HTTP_HOST}\" pattern=\"^example\\.com$\" />\n                    </conditions>\n                    <action type=\"Redirect\" url=\"https://www.example.com{REQUEST_URI}\" redirectType=\"Permanent\" />\n                </rule>\n\n                <!-- Redirect HTTP to HTTPS -->\n                <rule name=\"HTTP to HTTPS\" stopProcessing=\"true\">\n                    <match url=\"(.*)\" />\n                    <conditions>\n                        <add input=\"{HTTPS}\" pattern=\"off\" ignoreCase=\"true\" />\n                    </conditions>\n                    <action type=\"Redirect\" url=\"https://{HTTP_HOST}{REQUEST_URI}\" redirectType=\"Permanent\" />\n                </rule>\n\n                <!-- Remove index.aspx from URL -->\n                <rule name=\"Remove index.aspx\" stopProcessing=\"true\">\n                    <match url=\"^index\\.aspx$\" />\n                    <action type=\"Redirect\" url=\"/\" redirectType=\"Permanent\" />\n                </rule>\n            </rules>\n        </rewrite>\n\n        <!-- Static File Caching and Compression -->\n        <staticContent>\n            <!-- Image Caching -->\n            <clientCache cacheControlMode=\"UseMaxAge\" cacheControlMaxAge=\"30.00:00:00\" />\n            \n            <!-- MIME Types for Additional Image Formats -->\n            <mimeMap fileExtension=\".webp\" mimeType=\"image/webp\" />\n            <mimeMap fileExtension=\".avif\" mimeType=\"image/avif\" />\n        </staticContent>\n\n        <!-- Compression Settings -->\n        <httpCompression>\n            <dynamicTypes>\n                <add mimeType=\"text/*\" enabled=\"true\" />\n                <add mimeType=\"application/json\" enabled=\"true\" />\n                <add mimeType=\"application/xml\" enabled=\"true\" />\n            </dynamicTypes>\n            <staticTypes>\n                <add mimeType=\"text/*\" enabled=\"true\" />\n                <add mimeType=\"application/json\" enabled=\"true\" />\n                <add mimeType=\"application/xml\" enabled=\"true\" />\n                <add mimeType=\"image/svg+xml\" enabled=\"true\" />\n            </staticTypes>\n        </httpCompression>\n\n        <!-- Security Headers -->\n        <httpProtocol>\n            <customHeaders>\n                <add name=\"X-Frame-Options\" value=\"SAMEORIGIN\" />\n                <add name=\"X-XSS-Protection\" value=\"1; mode=block\" />\n                <add name=\"X-Content-Type-Options\" value=\"nosniff\" />\n                <add name=\"Strict-Transport-Security\" value=\"max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains\" />\n            </customHeaders>\n        </httpProtocol>\n    </system.webServer>\n\n    <!-- Custom Error Pages -->\n    <system.web>\n        <customErrors mode=\"On\">\n            <error statusCode=\"404\" redirect=\"~/error-404.aspx\" />\n            <error statusCode=\"500\" redirect=\"~/error-500.aspx\" />\n        </customErrors>\n    </system.web>\n</configuration>\n```\n\nHere's a breakdown of what this configuration does:\n\n1. Canonical URL Redirects:\n   - Redirects non-www to www\n   - Enforces HTTPS\n   - Removes index.aspx from URL\n\n2. Image Caching:\n   - Sets cache control for static files to 30 days\n   - Adds MIME types for WebP and AVIF formats\n\n3. Compression:\n   - Enables compression for text, JSON, and XML content\n   - Improves website performance\n\n4. Security Headers:\n   - Adds various security-related HTTP headers\n   - Prevents clickjacking\n   - Enables XSS protection\n   - Enforces HTTPS\n\n5. Custom Error Pages:\n   - Configures custom error pages for 404 and 500 errors\n\nAdditional Recommendations:\n\n1. Replace \"example.com\" with your actual domain\n2. Adjust cache duration as needed\n3. Modify security headers according to your requirements\n4. Create corresponding error pages (error-404.aspx, error-500.aspx)\n\nNotes:\n- This is for IIS, not Apache\n- Requires URL Rewrite and Dynamic Compression modules in IIS\n- Test thoroughly in a staging environment\n\nFor more specific requirements, you may need to customize this configuration further.",
